23
{
  name { An Underground Cave Entrance  }
  desc {
"  It would seem that the outpost may have more then one purpose.
The worn rock around the entrance of this cave is proof that at
some point in time, it was exposed to the elements.  It would
be ill advised to enter the cave without some source of light as
an erie darkness looms at the cave's entrance.  A bitter cold
draft eminates from the entrance.
  }
  exits {
	to { u, 18 }
	  info { door, closed, secret, hidden, autoclose }
	  keywords { board }
	to { 10, 24 }
	  keywords { cave }
  }
}

24
{
  name { Beyond the Entrance  }
  desc {
"  The lighting from the entrance has quickly given way to a
bitter cold darkness.  The granite walls are jagged and as cold
as ice.  Your breath crystalizes as you exhale.  The floor of
the cave is very slick from condensation build up.  A constant
dripping sound can be heard echoing from deep within the darkness.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 25 }
	to { u, 23 }
  }
}

25
{
  name { The Cave  }
  desc {
"  The wide shaft is quickly decending into the earth.  The bitter
cold is beginning to become more bearable as it has caused you
to lose most of the feeling in your body.  The footing is getting
worse as the temperature has dropped well below the freezing point.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { e, 26 }
	to { s, 24 }
  }
}

26
{
  name { A Small Landing  }
  desc {
"  The steep path has leveled off somewhat.  The passage is
much wider here then above or below.  Massive collections
of ice have accumulated at various points on the landing.
Something can be seen in the largest of what can only
be described as a gigantic ice mound.  Upon further
inspection a jaw bone can be seen through the dark blue ice.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { s, 27 }
	to { w, 25 }
  }
}

27
{
  name { The Dark Passage  }
  desc {
"  The darkness here is strange.  The thick black ice walls not only
do not reflect light, but seem to be absorbing it.  The air
temperature is well below freezing.  This cold dark world is no
place for the faint of heart.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 26 }
	to { w, 28 }
  }
}

28
{
  name { The Dark Passage  }
  desc {
"  The cold here drains life from all living things that enter it.
The passage to the west is narrowing.  To the east it is slightly
wider.  A faint humming eminates from the west.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { e, 27 }
	to { w, 29 }
  }
}

29
{
  name { The Dark Passage  }
  desc {
"  A gigantic black door blocks passage to the west.  Its smooth
dark surface is void of any imperfections.  Protruding from the
icy floor, directly in front of the door, a black cylinder rises.
The cylinder has a long enscription wrapping about its otherwise
smooth surface.  A tear shaped depression has been cut into the 
top of the device.  The door, or something behind it, is releasing
a deep humming sound.  From the size and magnitude of this door,
it is safe to assume that someone, or something, has placed this
door here to ensure no one goes any deeper through the passage.
A wave of fear engulfs you as you realize the door might also be
placed to block passage back to the surface ...
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { e, 28 }
	to { w, 30 }
	  key { 99003 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, pickproof, autoclose, autolock }
	  keywords { door }
  }
}

30
{
  name { The Dark Passage  }
  desc {
"  A light can be seen to the west.  The eastern portion of the
passage is blocked by a door lacking any signs of a keyhole.
A few small crates full of provisions sit stacked neatly to one
side of the passage.  A note has been attached to one of the
crates.  The crates are extremely thick and have been lined with
some fur for insulation against the bitter cold of the cave.
Frost has already begun to engulf the supplies.  The door is
emitting a low pulsing hum.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { note }
	desc { 
"  Make sure these supplies last.  We have staggered the time we are opening
the door now, so I can't give you the exact time.  We can not risk "him"
ever escaping.  As there is no way to open the door from your end, we can
be sure that there will be no surprises.  The Captain has asked for another
division to be deployed to assist with "his" keeping.  I have included some
thing that might help fight off the bitter cold.
	}
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { w, 31 }
  }
}

31
{
  name { The Center Chamber  }
  desc {
"  Sounds echo from all four chambers in each direction.  The
lighting is dim, and nothing can be seen down any of the four
paths.  A strange mix of warm air from the east, and blasts
of cold air from the east mix in a strange swirl of refreshing
breezes.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 32 }
	to { e, 30 }
	to { s, 33 }
	to { w, 34 }
  }
}

32
{
  name { A Dead End  }
  desc {
"  This short path leading from the chamber to the south has
not been completed.  It was not originally part of the cave, and
is one of the only attempts to mine in the cave.  Brilliant gems
sparkle in the low light.  A spherical hole sits half unburied
in the north wall.  The inside of the sphere glows with a dull
purple aura.  Upon further examination it is apparent that a great
heat source was present here at some point.  The rock has long
since cooled, but from the smooth continuous surface of the rock
it is clear that something here was hot enough to melt the solid
rock to a liquid state at some point.  Shards of the other half
of the sphere lay scattered about the floor of the surrounding area.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { s, 31 }
  }
}

33
{
  name { A Sleeping Chamber  }
  desc {
"  A stone slab sits raised from the floor on the eastern
wall.  Worn blankets cover the stone slab allowing for
some comfort for those who rest their bones here.  A large
wooden barrel sits full next to the bed.  Shelves sit
covered with vials, books, parchments, and wands.  A small
collection of scrolls and manuscripts sit upon a large
stone table bearing a relief of a dancing flame surrounding
a half moon.  Wild surges of magic surge forth from a small
glowing chest hovering in the corner.
  }
  flags { dark, no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 31 }
  }
}

34
{
  name { The Concentration Room  }
  desc {
"  The circular room is dominated by the blackwater pool that
sits motionless in the center of the room.  As you approach
the water your light source reveals a hideous creature sitting
motionless at the bottom of the small pool.  There are three
men floating about the room in a circular pattern.  The pool
casts its black aura about the room engulfing all but the men.
With their arms crossed, and eyes closed, it is obvious that
they are deep in meditation.  Could it be their magic keeping
the beast dormant in the blackwater?
  }
  flags { dark, private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { e, 31 }
	to { d, 35 }
	  key { 99004 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, secret, pickproof, autoclose, autolock }
	  keywords { pool }
  }
}

35
{
  name { Below the Pool  }
  desc {
"  The blackwater pool above sits magically suspended over this
prison of no walls.  The platform beneath your feet has been
engulfed by broken bones and pieces of shattered armor.  A
chasm, as dark as night, extends down past your depth of sight.
An awful silence lingers as the darkness swallows every sound
you make.
  }
  flags { dark, indoors, summon_trap, blue_glow, private, no_sum }
  exits {
	to { u, 34 }
	  key { 99004 }
	  info { door, closed, locked, secret, pickproof, autoclose, autolock }
	  keywords { pool }
  }
}
